TODO  (TinyCC upstream bug list — converted to a checklist)

Status verified 2026-06-27 against the built compiler (build/tcc -Iinclude -Bbuild),
cross-checked vs gcc -std=gnu99. Legend:
  [x] verified fixed (reproducer passes, matches gcc)
  [ ] still open / reproduces
  [~] not actionable here (design note, arch-specific, or deliberate non-goal)
Full reproducers + investigation scaffold: see TODO-BUGS-INVESTIGATION.md

Bugs:

- [~] i386 fastcall is mostly wrong
       arch-specific; no-op on x86_64 host. See INVESTIGATION §C.
- [~] FPU st(0) is left unclean (kwisatz haderach). Incompatible with
      optimized gcc/msc code
       arch-specific (i386 x87). See INVESTIGATION §C.
- [x] see transparent union pb in /urs/include/sys/socket.h
       DONE: __attribute__((transparent_union)) implemented (tccgen.c
       transparent_union_member + gfunc_param_typed; SymAttr.transp_union;
       TOK_TRANSPARENT_UNION1/2). 3-way test tests2/190. Matches gcc/clang.
- [x] precise behaviour of typeof with arrays ? (__put_user macro)
      but should suffice for most cases)
       typeof(array) preserves element type + size (matches gcc).
- [x] handle '? x, y : z' in unsized variable initialization (',' is
      considered incorrectly as separator in preparser)
       comma now parsed as operator inside ?: ; int a[]={c?1,2:3} -> 2.
- [x] transform functions to function pointers in function parameters
      (net/ipv4/ip_output.c)
       function-typed params decay to pointers and call correctly.
- [x] fix function pointer type display
       type_to_str renders 'int (*)(int, double)', 'int (**)(...)' correctly in
       'cannot convert' diagnostics (only a cosmetic 'extern ' storage-class
       leak remains, not fn-ptr-specific). INVESTIGATION §E.
- [x] check section alignment in C
       __attribute__((aligned(64))) honored at runtime.
- [x] fix invalid cast in comparison 'if (v == (int8_t)v)'
       correct results for in-range and out-of-range values (matches gcc).
- [x] finish varargs.h support (gcc 3.2 testsuite issue)
       <stdarg.h> va_start/va_arg/va_end work.
- [~] fix static functions declared inside block
       standard form ('static int f(void);' at block scope) is correctly
       rejected like gcc; the GNU "nested function" reading is a large
       trampoline-based extension, deliberately unsupported. INVESTIGATION §E.
- [x] fix multiple unions init
       union U a[2]={{.i=1},{.c='A'}} -> 1 65 (matches gcc).
- [~] make libtcc fully reentrant (except for the compilation stage itself).
       large separate project.
- [x] struct/union/enum definitions in nested scopes (see also Debian bug #770657)
       sibling-block redeclaration of struct S works (matches gcc).
- [x] __STDC_IEC_559__: float f(void) { static float x = 0.0 / 0.0; return x; }
       compile-time 0.0/0.0 -> NaN, returned correctly.
- [~] memory may be leaked after errors (longjmp).
       large; error-path lifetime audit, not a point fix.

Portability:

- [~] it is assumed that int is 32-bit and sizeof(int) == 4
- [~] int is used when host or target size_t would make more sense
- [~] TCC handles target floating-point (fp) values using the host's fp
      arithmetic, which is simple and fast but may lead to exceptions
      and inaccuracy and wrong representations when cross-compiling
       (all three: architectural design notes, not point fixes — INVESTIGATION §D)

Linking:

- [~] static linking (-static) does sort of work
	works with musl libc
	glibc requires libc.so even when statically linked (very bad, but not
	up to tcc)

Bound checking:

- [~] fix bound exit on RedHat 7.3
- [~] setjmp is not supported properly in bound checking.
- [~] fix bound check code with '&' on local variables (currently done
      only for local arrays).
- [~] bound checking and float/long long/struct copy code. bound
      checking and symbol + offset optimization
       (all bcheck items: gated by TCC_CONFIG_BCHECK; old, hard to reproduce on a
        modern host — defer unless bcheck work is requested. INVESTIGATION §D)

Missing features:

- [~] disable-asm and disable-bcheck options
       disable-bcheck EXISTS (TCC_CONFIG_BCHECK). disable-asm DECLINED after
       scoping: the asm call sites in tccgen.c (asm_instr 7495, asm_global_instr
       8792, asm_label_instr 8854/def 5011) and parse_asm_str are NOT guarded by
       #ifdef CONFIG_TCC_ASM, so the tree does not build without asm today.
       Adding the guards is bounded but invasive on the parser hot path AND
       disables asm-label symbol renaming (used in real headers), for marginal
       benefit, and contradicts the documented CMake policy (CMakeLists.txt:1067,
       "not a config.h flag"). INVESTIGATION §D.
- [x] __builtin_expect()
       implemented; likely()/unlikely() idioms work.
- [x] atexit (Nigel Horne)
       handler runs after main.
- [ ] C99: add complex types (gcc 3.2 testsuite issue)
       REPRODUCES: '_Complex is not yet supported'. LARGE feature. INVESTIGATION §B2.
- [x] postfix compound literals (see 20010124-1.c)
       ((struct S){.a=3,.b=4}).b -> 4.
- [~] interactive mode / integrated debugger
       large separate project.

Optimizations:

- [~] suppress specific anonymous symbol handling
- [~] more parse optimizations (=even faster compilation)
- [~] memory alloc optimizations (=even faster compilation)
- [~] optimize VT_LOCAL + const
- [~] better local variables handling (needed for other targets)
       (optimization wishlist; not bugs)

Not critical:

- [~] C99: fix multiple compound literals inits in blocks (ISOC99
      normative example - only relevant when using gotos! -> must add
      boolean variable to tell if compound literal was already
      initialized).
- [~] add PowerPC generator and improve codegen for RISC (need
      to suppress VT_LOCAL and use a base register instead).
- [x] fix preprocessor symbol redefinition
       identical redefine = silent, conflicting = "X redefined" warning (matches gcc).
- [~] add portable byte code generator and interpreter for other
      unsupported architectures.
- [~] C++: variable declaration in for, minimal 'class' support.
- [~] win32: __intxx. use resolve for bchecked malloc et al.
      check exception code (exception filter func).
- [x] handle void (__attribute__() *ptr)()
       attribute on a function-pointer declarator parses & assigns (verified
       with __attribute__((stdcall)) on a void(*)(void)).
- [~] VLAs are implemented in a way that is not compatible with signals:
      http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/tinycc-devel/2015-11/msg00018.html

Fixed (probably):

- bug with defines:
    #define spin_lock(lock) do { } while (0)
    #define wq_spin_lock spin_lock
    #define TEST() wq_spin_lock(a)
- typedefs can be structure fields
- see bugfixes.diff + improvement.diff from Daniel Glockner
- long long constant evaluation
- add alloca()
- gcc '-E' option.
- #include_next support for /usr/include/limits ?
- function pointers/lvalues in ? : (linux kernel net/core/dev.c)
- win32: add __stdcall, check GetModuleHandle for dlls.
- macro substitution with nested definitions (ShangHongzhang)
- with "-run" and libtcc, a PLT is now built.
- '-E' option was improved
- packed attribute is now supported
- ARM and ARM64 code generators have been added.
